      "side": 1,
      "message": "At first I thought you were right, but then I didn\u0027t understand why I didn\u0027t get yelled at by `valgrind` during my tests. After a closer look, it seems `*envp` is never pointing to `environ` AFAICT. `parse_args` gets called in `minijail0.c` this way:\n\n  char **envp \u003d NULL;\n  int consumed \u003d parse_args(j, argc, argv, environ,                                                                                                       \n    \u0026exit_immediately, \u0026elftype,                                                                                                  \n    \u0026preload_path, \u0026envp);\n    \nSo as far as `parse_args` is concerned, its `*envp` is `NULL`.\nNow, it doesn\u0027t cost anything to add the check you\u0027re suggesting, just in case at some point we change how parse_args gets called, so I implemented your suggestion nevertheless, if that\u0027s alright.\n\nIn digging this comment, I fixed a bug I introduced in the previous patchset, when reworking the \"clear_env\" matter: now, when `--env-reset` and `--env-add` are NOT used, the parent\u0027s env is correctly copied over the child. Sorry I missed that.",
